---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="About Turf Tech HQ — who we are and why we created this landscaping resource."
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-16">
    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 mb-12">
      <div class="md:w-64 flex-shrink-0">
        <img
          src="/author.jpg"
          alt="Chris VanDoren"
          class="w-full rounded-2xl shadow-md object-cover aspect-square"
        />
      </div>
      <div>
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-2 font-heading">Meet Chris VanDoren</h1>
        <p class="text-lg font-medium text-primary mb-4">Landscape Professional & Founder of Turf Tech HQ</p>
        <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
          Chris VanDoren is a certified landscape professional and the founder of Turf Tech HQ. With over 18 years of experience in both residential and commercial landscaping, Chris has designed, installed, and maintained everything from small urban gardens to sprawling estate grounds and corporate campuses. He earned his landscape architecture degree and is a Certified Landscape Professional (CLP) through the National Association of Landscape Professionals. After building and running a successful landscaping company for 12 years, Chris created Turf Tech HQ to help both professionals and homeowners make smarter decisions about lawn care, irrigation, hardscaping, and outdoor living spaces. He lives in Colorado, where the altitude and dry climate keep his landscaping skills sharp.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 font-heading">About Turf Tech HQ</h2>

    <p class="text-lg text-text-muted mb-6">
      Every lawn is different — the soil beneath it, the climate above it, the trees shading it, the kids and dogs running across it. One-size-fits-all lawn advice doesn't work, and that's exactly why Turf Tech HQ exists. We provide region-specific, science-backed guidance that accounts for your actual growing conditions instead of recycling generic tips from a gardening almanac.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 font-heading">Our Mission</h2>
    <p class="text-text-muted mb-6">
      A great lawn isn't about spending the most money — it's about understanding what your grass actually needs and doing the right thing at the right time. We help you build a lawn care plan that works with your soil type, grass species, and local climate, not against it. Less guesswork, fewer wasted weekends, and a yard you actually enjoy spending time in.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 font-heading">What We Cover</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-text-muted space-y-2 mb-6">
      <li>Lawn care, mowing, and seasonal maintenance</li>
      <li>Garden design, plant selection, and bed installation</li>
      <li>Irrigation systems and watering best practices</li>
      <li>Tree and shrub care, pruning, and trimming</li>
      <li>Soil health, fertilization, and weed control</li>
      <li>Tool reviews and product recommendations</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 font-heading">A Note on Safety</h2>
    <p class="text-text-muted mb-6">
      Landscaping work often involves power tools, chemicals, and heavy lifting. Always follow manufacturer guidelines for equipment, wear appropriate protective gear, and consult a professional for work involving large trees, irrigation systems, or grading that exceeds your experience level. The information on Turf Tech HQ is for educational purposes and does not replace professional judgement.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 font-heading">Affiliate Disclosure</h2>
    <p class="text-text-muted">
      Turf Tech HQ participates in the Amazon Associates program. When you purchase products through links on this site, we may earn a small commission at no extra cost to you. This helps us keep the content free and up to date.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
